{
  "analysis": "We are in /app with pMARS available. The task is to write my_warrior.red that achieves specified win rates against five classic warriors in warriors/. We need 75+ wins out of 100 against stone.red, paper.red, and vampire.red, and at least 33+ wins against snake.red and g2-clear.red. A robust approach against these classics is an aggressive SPL/JMP/DAT core-clear 'carpet bomber' that quickly overwrites memory and kills processes. This tends to perform very well versus stone, paper, and vampire, and should achieve at least a modest win rate versus snake and g2-clear. We'll inspect the opponent files to understand their patterns, create our warrior, then test using pmars batch mode against each opponent and verify the win rates. If initial results are close but not sufficient, we can iterate by adjusting boot distance or increasing number of clear processes.",
  "plan": "1) List directory and inspect warriors to confirm availability and see code patterns. 2) Create my_warrior.red implementing a fast SPL/JMP/DAT carpet clear with multiple spawned processes and a booted pointer to paint the core away from our code. 3) Test versus each opponent with pmars -b -r 100 -f my_warrior.red warriors/<opponent>.red and inspect results. 4) If any threshold is not met, adjust parameters (e.g., number of SPL spawns, boot distance, block stride) and retest until thresholds are met.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "ls -la\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "ls -la warriors\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "sed -n '1,200p' warriors/stone.red\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "sed -n '1,200p' warriors/paper.red\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "sed -n '1,200p' warriors/vampire.red\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "sed -n '1,200p' warriors/snake.red\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "sed -n '1,200p' warriors/g2-clear.red\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > my_warrior.red << 'EOF'\n;redcode-94\n;name CarpetClear Six\n;author ChatGPT\n;strategy Aggressive SPL/JMP/DAT carpet clear across core with multiple processes\n;assert 1\n\norg start\n\nBOOTDIST   equ   2000     ; initial painting starts well away from our code\n\nstart      spl   clear     ; spawn multiple painters for speed\n           spl   clear\n           spl   clear\n           spl   clear\n           spl   clear\n           jmp   clear\n           dat   0, 0\n\nptr        dat   0, start+BOOTDIST  ; B-field points to current paint target\n\nclear      mov   c0, @ptr           ; copy 3-instruction kill carpet\n           mov   c1, @ptr\n           mov   c2, @ptr\n           add   #3, ptr            ; advance paint pointer\n           jmp   clear\n\nc0         spl   0, 0               ; entering carpet spawns, slowing enemy\nc1         jmp  -1, 0               ; loop inside carpet\nc2         dat   0, 0               ; eventual kill\nEOF\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "pmars -b -r 100 -f my_warrior.red warriors/stone.red\n",
      "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "pmars -b -r 100 -f my_warrior.red warriors/paper.red\n",
      "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "pmars -b -r 100 -f my_warrior.red warriors/vampire.red\n",
      "duration": 2.0
    },
    {
